		<part id="motivation">
			<title>Using Digital Building Blocks</title>
			<slide id="building-blocks">
				<title>APIs represent Digital Building Blocks</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Every capability is made available through an API</li>
					<li>New capabilities are built on existing capabilities</li>
					<li>The focus is to make <em>all capabilities reusable</em></li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="internal">
				<title>APIs as Internal Componentization</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Moving from integration to interconnection (IT modernization)</li>
					<li>Decoupling components and their development cycles and speed</li>
					<li>Improving capability reuse across the organization</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="external">
				<title>APIs as External Interfaces</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Direct API monetization (selling APIs as products)</li>
					<li>Interaction with partners (easier integration)</li>
					<li>Attracting new business (outsourcing innovation)</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="business-model-overview">
				<title>API Business Model Overview</title>
				<img href="https://www.programmableweb.com/news/programmablewebs-guide-to-modern-api-business-models/analysis/2020/10/26" src="api-business-models.png" class="fullsize"/>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="journey">
			<title>The API Journey</title>
			<slide id="vision">
				<title>From Vision to Strategy to Program to Platform</title>
				<ul>
					<li>The <em>API Vision</em> identifies API as enablers for digitalization</li>
					<li>The <em>API Strategy</em> tells the story of how to make APIs a reality</li>
					<li>The <em>API Program</em> makes sure that the strategy is executed</li>
					<li>The <em>API Platform</em> provides support for creating and using APIs</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="kpis">
				<title>Measure What Matters: KPIs for APIs</title>
				<img src="charles-goodhart.jpg" title="Charles Goodhart of Goodhart's Law: &quot;When a measure becomes a target, it ceases to be a good measure.&quot;" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uKVZ3Zxi1no" style="float: right ; height : 65% ; margin : 0% 4% 4% 4% ; "/>
				<ul>
					<li>APIs aren't the goal</li>
					<li>Success should be measured at the business level</li>
					<li><em>Low-level metrics</em> are useful for improving operations</li>
					<li><em>Business-level metrics</em> are useful for measuring success</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
